<font color="#FF0000">LESSONS LEARNED?</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan  4 19:05:02 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Did we learn from Vietnam to treat veterans better?  Maybe not!  Is it true that the disease afflicting many Gulf War veterans, which may well have been caused by captured chemical weapons that were released into the atmosphere when the U.S. Army blew up the bunkers they were in, is still not being treated effectively by the Department of Veterans“ Affairs?  Does the Government still say that this disease does not exist?  Finally, is it true that many Gulf War veterans are having difficulty finding satisfactory employment?
